{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1041", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "The Indian herbal medicine market is expected to reach USD 371.45 billion by 2030.", "citations": {"21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430": 1.0}}, {"text": "Indian researchers are studying a Himalayan plant with antiviral properties for COVID-19 treatment.", "citations": {"3806d0c3-e2dc-4730-b3ad-3e74c8dcc952_937003941": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurveda, a traditional Indian medicine system, uses turmeric to help manage Type 2 diabetes.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "A pilot project suggests using Ayurveda to treat diabetes by controlling blood sugar.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ashwagandha reduces anxiety, stress, and fatigue, and improves muscle strength.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "A study on Ashwagandha for long Covid involves 2,000 participants taking 1,000mg daily.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "The study is funded by India's Ministry of Ayush and supported by the WHO.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "BGR-34 is a herbal diabetes formulation containing daruharidra, gudmar, methi, and vijayasar that helps reduce sugar levels and addresses obesity.", "citations": {"c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663": 1.0}}, {"text": "Researchers have studied 21 herbs and identified 400 medicinal plants with anti-diabetic properties for diabetes.", "citations": {"c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663": 1.0}}, {"text": "The WHO is supporting research on traditional Indian medicine, including Ashwagandha for long Covid.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "Institutions like the All India Institute of Ayurveda and the National Institutes of Unani and Homoeopathy develop and test Indian herbal medicines.", "citations": {"7c35d59b-3417-4232-97ca-d685314ade3f_354844377": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Jawaharlal Institute of Postgraduate Medical Education and Research and the All India Institute of Medical Sciences have collaborated on research into herbal plants for treating diseases like diabetes.", "citations": {"c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663": 1.0}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization has proposed a global centre for traditional medicine in India, possibly in Hyderabad.", "citations": {"98cb1295-a33e-4e2b-8dc2-ad49132f6a98_528404869": 1.0}}, {"text": "The WHO centre for traditional medicine, based in Jamnagar, India, aims to set research standards and connect global practitioners.", "citations": {"cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic plants can be contaminated with heavy metals, necessitating quality control and standardization.", "citations": {"e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of Indian herbal medicines can have potential risks, including interactions and contamination with heavy metals.", "citations": {"e482bd93-fd7e-446b-ba03-e2926e0a5753_419383171": 1.0}}, {"text": "More research is needed to understand the risks and benefits of Indian herbal medicines and mitigate risks in clinical practice.", "citations": {"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_114004108": 1.0}}, {"text": "Traditional Indian medicine has potential as a safe and effective treatment, but further research is needed to understand its risks and benefits.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0, "ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 0.5, "e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 0.25}}], "references": ["98cb1295-a33e-4e2b-8dc2-ad49132f6a98_528404869", "e482bd93-fd7e-446b-ba03-e2926e0a5753_419383171", "cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576", "3806d0c3-e2dc-4730-b3ad-3e74c8dcc952_937003941", "57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334", "262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_114004108", "c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663", "7c35d59b-3417-4232-97ca-d685314ade3f_354844377", "21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430", "e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793", "ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1042", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "The Indian herbal medicine market is growing rapidly, with a projected CAGR of 8.02% during the forecast period, and the market size is expected to reach USD 371.45 billion by 2030.", "citations": {"21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430": 1.0}}, {"text": "The herbal medicine market size was valued at USD 201.06 billion in 2022, indicating a growing demand for herbal medicines.", "citations": {"21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430": 1.0}}, {"text": "Herbal medicines made from natural ingredients are used to treat various diseases, offering a safer alternative to pharmaceutical drugs.", "citations": {"21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430": 1.0}}, {"text": "India has key companies like Cultivator Natural Products and Himalaya Global that are involved in the production and research of herbal medicines.", "citations": {"21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430": 1.0}}, {"text": "The COVID-19 pandemic has boosted the demand for herbal medicines and supplements, with many people turning to traditional remedies for prevention and treatment.", "citations": {"21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430": 1.0}}, {"text": "Neem tree extract has been found to have anti-parasitic, antiviral, and anti-inflammatory properties, making it effective against diseases like COVID-19 and malaria.", "citations": {"290cabe3-2353-4112-bf92-b9a0914e327b_142802437": 1.0}}, {"text": "The neem tree extract has been shown to target viral proteins, reduce illness risk, and decrease virus replication, making it a promising candidate for the treatment of emerging variants.", "citations": {"290cabe3-2353-4112-bf92-b9a0914e327b_142802437": 1.0}}, {"text": "A Himalayan plant, Rhododendron arboreum, has been found to have antiviral activity against COVID-19, with researchers from IIT studying its phytochemicals for potential synergistic activity.", "citations": {"3806d0c3-e2dc-4730-b3ad-3e74c8dcc952_937003941": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurveda, a traditional system of medicine, has been found to be effective in treating Type 2 diabetes, with turmeric being a key ingredient used to maintain blood sugar levels.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic remedies have minimal side effects and are in high demand, with many people opting for lifestyle modification and detoxifying treatments to manage their health.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "Cardamom has been found to have anti-inflammatory properties, making it effective in the treatment of diseases like cancer, with a cardamom-based nutraceutical called Recovereez being launched for health benefits.", "citations": {"57ef30c9-1e84-4bf5-8e27-b1dab39904f6_389634030": 1.0}}, {"text": "Basil, cinnamon, fenugreek, turmeric, and garlic are some of the Indian herbs that have been found to help prevent diabetes and hypertension, with eugenol in tulsi opposing chemicals that constrict blood vessels.", "citations": {"6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965": 1.0}}, {"text": "Certain Indian herbs have been found to combat metabolic stress and psychological stress, providing immunity and nourishing nutrients to the body.", "citations": {"6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965": 1.0}}, {"text": "Pond seed has been found to eliminate malaria and gastric issues, with Indian herbs being used to treat diseases like gout, joint pain, and intestinal obstruction.", "citations": {"8e3e4556-527c-40ba-ae06-782bf7919d8e_80140370": 1.0}}, {"text": "HealthRoots has launched herbal products for headaches and stress, using rare international herbs and focusing on treating migraines, arthritis, and diabetes with Ayurvedic remedies.", "citations": {"9070a5c5-cd76-46ba-8c07-33e91b535e03_742183461": 1.0}}, {"text": "The company uses the Rhodiola plant to make a drug called Redrive Am, which increases endurance and reduces stress, with HealthRoots inspecting ingredients for environmental harmony.", "citations": {"9070a5c5-cd76-46ba-8c07-33e91b535e03_742183461": 1.0}}, {"text": "Researchers have identified 400 medicinal plants with anti-diabetic properties, with 21 herbal plants having prominent anti-hyperglycemic action, and a herbal formulation called BGR-34 being used for diabetes management.", "citations": {"c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663": 1.0}}, {"text": "BGR-34 contains compounds from daruharidra, gudmar, methi, and vijayasar, and has been found to reduce sugar levels and address obesity, with many drugs for diabetes being based on Ayurvedic formulations.", "citations": {"c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ashwagandha has been found to boost energy and immune system, reducing anxiety and stress in patients, with a clinical trial being conducted to study its effects on long Covid symptoms.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "The trial, funded by the Ministry of Ayush of the Indian Government and supported by the World Health Organisation, will involve 2,000 people taking 500mg Ashwagandha tablets twice a day.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "Herbs and spices have been found to have anti-inflammatory properties, with Ayurveda using them for health and disease prevention, and polyphenols in herbs and spices acting as prebiotics to maintain gut homeostasis.", "citations": {"dafa9da5-38cf-4c0c-8b4f-09b814ce1c2e_365620837": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ginger and turmeric have been found to increase beneficial gut microbes, with spices promoting SCFA production and having anti-obesity effects, and reducing cancer risk by acting as anti-inflammatory compounds.", "citations": {"dafa9da5-38cf-4c0c-8b4f-09b814ce1c2e_365620837": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurveda has been studied for allergic rhinitis and diabetes, with high-quality research being difficult due to the unique treatment approach of Ayurveda, which uses diet, herbs, and massage for treatment.", "citations": {"e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 1.0}}, {"text": "The National Center for Complementary and Integrative Health has studied Ayurveda, with Ayurveda plant combinations potentially containing heavy metals and causing heavy metal poisoning.", "citations": {"e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Indian government is integrating Ayurveda with modern medicine and has plans to operationalize 12,500 Ayush centers by 2023-24.", "citations": {"2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayush system promotes a healthy lifestyle for school children and Ayush mobile medical units are being implemented.", "citations": {"2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has released Rs 719.70 crore to southern states under the National AYUSH Mission (NAM) to provide Ayush healthcare services nationwide.", "citations": {"2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955": 1.0}}, {"text": "Seventeen Integrated Ayush hospitals have been supported in southern states, and six Ayush hospitals are operational in the region.", "citations": {"2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic medicine uses a holistic approach to treat the body, mind, and spirit, and essential herbs have been used in Ayurvedic practice for millennia.", "citations": {"2b3d1f11-a45e-4ea7-ae82-52bef644a2c4_103444846": 1.0}}, {"text": "Prajna Ayurveda herbals combine traditional use with clinical science, and four essential herbs - Triphala, Ashwagandha, Brahmi, and Guggul - make up Prajna Ayurveda formulas.", "citations": {"2b3d1f11-a45e-4ea7-ae82-52bef644a2c4_103444846": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic remedies have been found to be effective in maintaining blood sugar levels in Type 2 diabetes patients, and turmeric is one of the herbs used in Ayurveda to treat diabetes.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic approach to diabetes management includes lifestyle modification and detoxifying therapies, and pilot projects have suggested the use of Ayurveda treatment for diabetes management.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "Triphala, an Ayurvedic medicine, has antioxidant properties and can reduce cholesterol and blood pressure levels, promote hair growth, and improve digestion and nutrient absorption.", "citations": {"853e714d-b896-4c52-890d-452b340c21ab_816014942": 1.0}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization recognizes Ayurveda science and practice, and the UAE provides insurance coverage for Ayurveda benefits, with hospitals like LLH Hospital Abu Dhabi establishing Vidiashala Ayurveda Center.", "citations": {"85b55ba7-26c9-41e1-97df-36006bab38d5_534963215": 1.0}}, {"text": "Vidiashala Ayurveda Centre treats chronic non-communicable diseases, arthritis, allergies, and asthma, and provides packages for detox, energy, and sleep assistance.", "citations": {"85b55ba7-26c9-41e1-97df-36006bab38d5_534963215": 1.0}}, {"text": "HealthRoots uses Ayurvedic herbs to prevent headaches and stress, and has launched products like Migoherb and Redrive Am to treat migraine headaches and reduce tiredness and stress.", "citations": {"9070a5c5-cd76-46ba-8c07-33e91b535e03_742183461": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic herbs like Rhodiola and Butterburr are used to derive Redrive Am and Migoherb, respectively, and HealthRoots focuses on treating rheumatoid arthritis and diabetes with Ayurveda.", "citations": {"9070a5c5-cd76-46ba-8c07-33e91b535e03_742183461": 1.0}}, {"text": "Researchers have identified 400 medicinal plants with anti-diabetic properties, and 21 herbal plants have been found to have prominent anti-hyperglycemic action.", "citations": {"c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663": 1.0}}, {"text": "BGR-34 is a herbal formulation that has been found to manage diabetes, and contains compounds from four medicinal herbs.", "citations": {"c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ashwagandha, an Ayurvedic herb, has been found to boost energy and immune system, reduce anxiety and stress, and improve muscle strength.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "A trial is being conducted to study the effects of Ashwagandha on long Covid symptoms, and the trial is funded by the Ministry of Ayush of the Indian Government.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurveda uses diet, herbs, and massage for treatment, and practitioners evaluate patients through symptoms and appearance.", "citations": {"e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, high-quality research on Ayurveda is difficult, and Ayurvedic plant combinations may contain heavy metals, which can cause heavy metal poisoning as a side effect.", "citations": {"e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic medicines have been linked to lead poisonings in some cases, and symptoms of lead poisoning include fatigue and irritability.", "citations": {"e482bd93-fd7e-446b-ba03-e2926e0a5753_419383171": 1.0}}, {"text": "Regulation of herbal supplements is lacking in the UK, and Ayurvedic practitioners may not have standardized training, which can lead to liver failure if Ayurvedic remedies are not used properly.", "citations": {"e740d601-b53e-4635-9992-3e8936b06287_572584438": 1.0}}, {"text": "Alternative medicine, including Ayurveda, uses herbs for treatment, and modern medicine requires international approval for treatment.", "citations": {"fa0958e4-596b-4a96-9beb-00fb0a1572ce_874250916": 1.0}}, {"text": "Honey and bee venom have a role in healing in modern medicine, and alternative medicine treats chronic diseases.", "citations": {"fa0958e4-596b-4a96-9beb-00fb0a1572ce_874250916": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Telangana government has invested Rs 10 crore in the Nature Cure Hospital, which is a significant investment in the field of traditional medicine.", "citations": {"00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has also planned to build 50-bed Ayush hospitals in three districts, which will provide better healthcare facilities to the people.", "citations": {"00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542": 1.0}}, {"text": "There are four research hospitals for Ayush in Telangana, which are working towards the development of traditional medicine.", "citations": {"00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Dr BRKR Government Ayurvedic Medical College has made significant contributions to the treatment of black fungus, which is a serious disease.", "citations": {"00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic doctors are being trained as Mid-Level Health Professionals, which will help in providing better healthcare services to the people.", "citations": {"00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has also planned to build a government centre near the Jindal Ayurveda Hospital, which will provide more facilities for the patients.", "citations": {"00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Ayurveda hospital in Siddipet is being linked to a medical college, which will help in providing better education and training to the students.", "citations": {"00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Jammu and Kashmir government has established an Ayurvedic Medical College & Hospital at Akhnoor, which is a significant step towards the development of traditional medicine.", "citations": {"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Unani Medical College & Hospital at Ganderbal has also been established, which will provide better healthcare facilities to the people.", "citations": {"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677": 1.0}}, {"text": "There are 442 AYUSH Dispensaries in J&K, which have been upgraded to provide better services to the people.", "citations": {"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677": 1.0}}, {"text": "The National AYUSH Mission has strengthened the AYUSH secondary healthcare system, which has helped in providing better healthcare facilities to the people.", "citations": {"0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Aghoreshwar Bhagwan Ram Yoga and Naturopathy Research Centre has", "citations": {}}], "references": ["e482bd93-fd7e-446b-ba03-e2926e0a5753_419383171", "3806d0c3-e2dc-4730-b3ad-3e74c8dcc952_937003941", "21cad66b-e3e9-4d51-bf12-0c7b485aee69_976945430", "853e714d-b896-4c52-890d-452b340c21ab_816014942", "6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965", "c7759200-92d0-49c0-b063-d504fc07f1ae_307926663", "2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955", "dafa9da5-38cf-4c0c-8b4f-09b814ce1c2e_365620837", "ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076", "290cabe3-2353-4112-bf92-b9a0914e327b_142802437", "fa0958e4-596b-4a96-9beb-00fb0a1572ce_874250916", "85b55ba7-26c9-41e1-97df-36006bab38d5_534963215", "e740d601-b53e-4635-9992-3e8936b06287_572584438", "0a2d1ec2-1ee6-4f95-9d00-3b75d29dc6d0_100317677", "57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334", "8e3e4556-527c-40ba-ae06-782bf7919d8e_80140370", "e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793", "2b3d1f11-a45e-4ea7-ae82-52bef644a2c4_103444846", "57ef30c9-1e84-4bf5-8e27-b1dab39904f6_389634030", "9070a5c5-cd76-46ba-8c07-33e91b535e03_742183461", "00ff3c60-1eb7-4c91-b728-9b4ccfd95b68_28827542"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1047", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Ocean acidification affects marine life by dissolving the calcium carbonate shells and skeletons of organisms like fish and shellfish due to low pH levels.", "citations": {"0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487": 1.0}}, {"text": "The impact of ocean acidification on cephalopods, like cuttlefish and octopuses, is not well-studied.", "citations": {"5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification can affect the development and growth of marine species, including cephalopod prey like shrimp and crustaceans.", "citations": {"eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean warming can affect cephalopod species, like octopuses, by altering their vision, metabolism, and reproduction.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification and warming can lead to population collapse in species like shrimp, threatening cephalopod populations that rely on them for food.", "citations": {"eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change can significantly impact cephalopod populations by disrupting habitats, altering behavior, and affecting ecosystem energy balance.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification, a result of global warming, affects marine life, including cephalopods, altering their distribution, behavior, and ecology.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change affects the nervous system and energy balance of ecosystems, impacting cephalopod populations.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification and warming can significantly impact marine ecosystems, including cephalopods, although specific effects on them are not well understood.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "More research is needed to understand ocean acidification's impact on cephalopod populations and develop effective conservation strategies.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Addressing ocean acidification is crucial to mitigate climate change's impact on marine life, including cephalopods, and protect ocean health.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Reducing CO2 emissions helps preserve marine ecosystems and species like cephalopods that are crucial to the food web.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification is a significant threat to marine life, including cephalopods, and action is needed to protect the health of our oceans.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}], "references": ["fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775", "5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131", "eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312", "f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611", "0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487", "f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1048", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Ocean acidification is a pressing issue that affects marine life, including cephalopods, by increasing the acidity of the water due to rising carbon dioxide emissions.", "citations": {"5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131": 1.0}}, {"text": "Cephalopods, such as octopuses, are impacted by ocean warming, which affects their vision due to heat stress, causing blurred vision and reduced protein production for vision.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification also affects the relatives of cephalopods, such as pteropods, which are crucial for the ocean environment and are sensitive to acidity, with winter sea butterflies being more vulnerable to acidification.", "citations": {"54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246": 1.0}}, {"text": "Pteropods, like sea butterflies, have different life cycles, and some species, such as L. rangii, have a survival advantage over others, like L. retroversa, in acidified waters.", "citations": {"54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification threatens the larvae of sea butterflies and can cause prolonged exposure to acidification to be harmful.", "citations": {"54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246": 1.0}}, {"text": "Cephalopods, including octopuses, are also affected by warmer waters, which can accelerate their metabolism, making them smaller, and changing their distribution areas.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Warmer oceans can also negatively affect octopus reproduction, reducing egg spawning numbers and causing entire broods to remain unhatched.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "While there is limited information on the direct effects of ocean acidification on cephalopod physiology and behavior, it is known that ocean acidification can impact animals with calcium carbonate skeletons, such as abalone and shrimp.", "citations": {"e915e068-38b7-4dcd-8beb-7150790db412_964077326": 1.0, "eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312": 0.5}}, {"text": "Abalone growth performance is affected by ocean acidification, with low CO2 buffering capacity impairing growth, and low calcium carbonate saturation state eroding shells.", "citations": {"e915e068-38b7-4dcd-8beb-7150790db412_964077326": 1.0}}, {"text": "Shrimp larvae are vulnerable to ocean acidification and warming, with lower survival rates and accelerated growth at high temperatures, and combined warming and acidification affecting egg-hatching success.", "citations": {"eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification and warming can have devastating effects on marine life, including cephalopods, and can lead to changes in ecosystem structure and function.", "citations": {"5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131": 1.0, "eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312": 0.5}}, {"text": "Seagrass meadows can help mitigate the effects of ocean acidification by increasing pH levels and reducing sea urchin larvae malformations.", "citations": {"72c97bcc-1d0e-4811-af80-28bb8339387c_827939974": 1.0}}, {"text": "Seagrass photosynthesis can alter seawater chemistry, aiding larval development at low pH and helping to prevent climate-driven biodiversity loss.", "citations": {"72c97bcc-1d0e-4811-af80-28bb8339387c_827939974": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, ocean acidification has far-reaching impacts on marine life beyond coral reefs, and it is essential to continue studying its effects to develop effective conservation strategies.", "citations": {"0bea86b1-eadb-4c2a-8d48-e3bb5ef5780a_203442634": 1.0}}], "references": ["54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246", "f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957", "eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312", "5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131", "72c97bcc-1d0e-4811-af80-28bb8339387c_827939974", "0bea86b1-eadb-4c2a-8d48-e3bb5ef5780a_203442634", "e915e068-38b7-4dcd-8beb-7150790db412_964077326"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1053", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "The US is the largest consumer of avocados, accounting for almost half of global demand.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "US avocado consumption quadrupled from 2002 to 2022, reaching 4.2 kg per capita.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico, with most of its production in Michoac\u00e1n, is the world's largest avocado producer.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico lost at least 300 square kilometers of forest to avocado plantations from 2018-2023 due to rising demand.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado cultivation consumes around 1,000 liters of water per kilogram, causing water shortages in countries like Mexico and Morocco.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "In Jalisco, Mexico, 1,100 trees disappear daily due to avocado plantation expansion.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production has brought economic benefits to local farming communities, particularly in countries like Mexico, through significant export revenue.", "citations": {"8ca9c8e9-43b5-47a1-b8c7-47fcb66e4530_31759721": 1.0}}, {"text": "The rising demand for avocados has led to social concerns, including impacts on local communities and farmer exploitation.", "citations": {"ed28e7a7-da90-4a40-b12e-0760be78ebed_839177627": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change may reduce avocado production by 40% by 2050 due to hotter and drier conditions.", "citations": {"c0a6998e-f6dc-4da7-9421-f8e7e575bd75_992753141": 1.0}}, {"text": "Governments and organizations can promote sustainable avocado farming by reducing water and chemical use and offering financial incentives.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "Consumers can promote sustainable avocado production by choosing products with certifications like Rainforest Alliance or Fairtrade.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global avocado industry has significant implications, requiring a concerted effort to promote sustainable production practices.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}], "references": ["c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865", "9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657", "0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651", "ed28e7a7-da90-4a40-b12e-0760be78ebed_839177627", "8ca9c8e9-43b5-47a1-b8c7-47fcb66e4530_31759721", "c0a6998e-f6dc-4da7-9421-f8e7e575bd75_992753141"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1054", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "The global demand for avocados has increased significantly over the past 20 years, with the US accounting for almost half of the world's avocado demand.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_55923929": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico is the world's largest producer of avocados, with 70% of its production coming from the state of Michoac\u00e1n.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "The majority of Mexico's avocados are exported to the US, where per capita consumption has increased to about 4.2 kg in 2022.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado cultivation is a profitable business in Mexico, but it has also caused significant deforestation, with at least 300 square kilometers of forest converted to avocado plantations from 2018-2023.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_55923929": 1.0}}, {"text": "The authorities in Mexico have announced that they will prevent the export of avocados from illegal farmland, in an effort to curb the environmental impact of avocado production.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production is a major export for Mexico, with the US being a significant market, and the country's per capita avocado consumption is 4.2 kg.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, the avocado industry in Mexico is also linked to criminal organizations, which vie for control of the avocado circulation rights, and illegal avocado cultivation is a significant problem.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "In Morocco, another major avocado-producing country, the water usage for avocado cultivation is a significant concern, with over 1,000 liters of water required to produce just one kilogram of avocados.", "citations": {"18665f57-7b47-4cae-9c9d-5fc30625182f_930516690": 1.0}}, {"text": "Morocco's agriculture sector accounts for over 80 percent of the country's groundwater, and the country is facing a severe water crisis due to drought and depletion.", "citations": {"18665f57-7b47-4cae-9c9d-5fc30625182f_930516690": 1.0}}, {"text": "To address these concerns, some companies, such as GLC Cerritos LLC, are implementing sustainable farming practices, including reforestation programs and certification by organizations such as the Rainforest Alliance.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "In Kenya, which is the largest avocado exporter in Africa, firms are investing in irrigation and green technology to mitigate the impacts of drought and conserve water.", "citations": {"a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_628665012": 1.0}}, {"text": "Sustainable practices, such as those promoted by the Rainforest Alliance, are crucial for reducing the environmental impact of avocado production and ensuring the long-term viability of the industry.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming requires significant amounts of water, with one study suggesting that it takes around 320 liters of water to grow just one avocado.", "citations": {"e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110": 1.0}}, {"text": "The transportation of avocados also has a significant carbon footprint, with one study estimating that it generates around 850 grams of carbon dioxide emissions per avocado.", "citations": {"e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110": 1.0}}, {"text": "In terms of social impacts, the growing demand for avocados has led to labor exploitation and food insecurity in some communities, particularly in Mexico, where indigenous communities have been displaced by avocado plantations.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, some companies and organizations are working to promote fair labor practices and support local farming communities, through initiatives such as Fair Trade certification and partnerships with smallholder farmers.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, while the growing demand for avocados has brought economic benefits to some countries, it has also raised significant environmental and social concerns, and sustainable farming practices are needed to reduce the impact of avocado production.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "The adoption of innovative technologies, such as precision irrigation and vertical farming, can help reduce the environmental footprint of avocado production and improve economic benefits for farmers.", "citations": {"1f4683f5-9dbf-4aae-a79c-8f8f1e7a6219_380413742": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, the high technology costs and lack of awareness about these technologies can be a barrier for small-scale farmers, and governments and organizations can play a crucial role in promoting their adoption.", "citations": {"b017efb6-7e06-4e6c-a458-4542d808f414_1017489960": 1.0}}, {"text": "Support mechanisms, such as financial incentives and training programs, are necessary to encourage small-scale farmers to adopt sustainable practices and innovative technologies.", "citations": {"147c627f-5c19-4ec4-b0cc-8fa5e3a80531_47619018": 1.0}}, {"text": "The promotion of sustainable avocado farming practices can reduce water use and chemical use, mitigate the environmental impact of avocado production, and improve the livelihoods of small-scale farmers.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production can have significant economic benefits, but it also requires careful consideration of the environmental and social impacts, and the adoption of sustainable practices to ensure the long-term viability of the industry.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "Governments, companies, and consumers must work together to promote sustainable avocado production and reduce the negative environmental and social impacts of the industry.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of certifications, such as Global G.A.P. and Rainforest Alliance, can help promote sustainable practices and ensure that avocados are produced in a responsible and environmentally friendly manner.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the future of the avocado industry depends on the adoption of sustainable practices and innovative technologies, and the commitment of governments, companies, and consumers to reducing the environmental and social impacts of avocado production.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}], "references": ["c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865", "0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651", "e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110", "0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_55923929", "a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_628665012", "b017efb6-7e06-4e6c-a458-4542d808f414_1017489960", "147c627f-5c19-4ec4-b0cc-8fa5e3a80531_47619018", "9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657", "695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478", "18665f57-7b47-4cae-9c9d-5fc30625182f_930516690", "1f4683f5-9dbf-4aae-a79c-8f8f1e7a6219_380413742"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1055", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Additives in salmon feed promote growth, improve health, and enhance nutritional value.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0, "8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 0.5}}, {"text": "Vitamins, minerals, and amino acids are added to salmon feed for a balanced diet.", "citations": {"7b6d93af-b92a-4b45-887d-a325a2c58a8a_905125272": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some countries use additives like antibiotics and pigments in fish, but their use is regulated due to concerns over resistance and pollution.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0, "5f7dda5c-2b54-4c63-9ea4-18daa1584e99_124643191": 0.5}}, {"text": "The use of antibiotics in salmon feed raises health concerns due to its potential to develop antibiotic-resistant bacteria and harm human health and the environment.", "citations": {"5f7dda5c-2b54-4c63-9ea4-18daa1584e99_124643191": 1.0, "ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 0.5}}, {"text": "In Norway, the use of antibiotics in salmon feed is strictly regulated to prevent antibiotic resistance.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "The European Union regulates salmon feed additives, banning certain antibiotics and requiring approval from the European Food Safety Authority.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The FDA regulates additives in US salmon farming, establishing guidelines for their use in animal feed.", "citations": {"9e48a690-5c54-4636-8239-aaba3d21be66_511986988": 1.0}}, {"text": "Sustainable additives like algae-based feed and probiotics are gaining popularity in salmon farming due to growing consumer awareness of environmental and health impacts.", "citations": {"602ea5be-7379-46ee-b2de-2ed786043337_589739900": 1.0, "19a72dbf-3566-40b4-ae9b-f102cbfc2f92_400224801": 0.5}}, {"text": "Probiotics and prebiotics are used in salmon farming to promote healthy gut microbiota, growth, and immunity.", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 1.0}}, {"text": "Salmon farming additives can accumulate pollutants like PCBs and dioxins, increasing cancer risk.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0, "f8eddc4e-9cfd-4bb9-94a0-29063736d129_533888044": 0.5}}, {"text": "Farmed salmon consumption is linked to increased risks of neurological and developmental problems due to mercury and pollutants.", "citations": {"f8eddc4e-9cfd-4bb9-94a0-29063736d129_533888044": 1.0}}, {"text": "Wild-caught salmon has lower levels of pollutants and higher levels of omega-3 fatty acids and vitamins.", "citations": {"2baaf058-afb6-492f-9d79-17be6266add5_891226991": 1.0}}, {"text": "Choosing wild-caught or sustainably farmed salmon can minimize the risks of consuming fat-soluble pollutants.", "citations": {"bc876b4e-8514-465e-9c42-49b5ae04c6c5_853119528": 1.0}}, {"text": "New feed additives are being developed to reduce salmon farming's reliance on wild-caught fish and improve sustainability.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "Stricter regulations on additives in salmon farming can have a positive impact on the environment and public health.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "Regulations for additives in salmon farming vary by country, impacting the industry.", "citations": {"adb6b376-1981-4027-92c3-fa738c1690ce_356480643": 1.0, "997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 0.5}}], "references": ["2baaf058-afb6-492f-9d79-17be6266add5_891226991", "f8eddc4e-9cfd-4bb9-94a0-29063736d129_533888044", "206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288", "bc876b4e-8514-465e-9c42-49b5ae04c6c5_853119528", "ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735", "7b6d93af-b92a-4b45-887d-a325a2c58a8a_905125272", "5f7dda5c-2b54-4c63-9ea4-18daa1584e99_124643191", "39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469", "8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648", "adb6b376-1981-4027-92c3-fa738c1690ce_356480643", "602ea5be-7379-46ee-b2de-2ed786043337_589739900", "9e48a690-5c54-4636-8239-aaba3d21be66_511986988", "19a72dbf-3566-40b4-ae9b-f102cbfc2f92_400224801", "997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922", "ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1056", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming is a common practice to enhance the growth and health of the fish, with additives such as vitamins, minerals, and amino acids being commonly used.", "citations": {"7b6d93af-b92a-4b45-887d-a325a2c58a8a_905125272": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some of the common additives used in salmon farming include soy proteins, wheat gluten, corn gluten meal, vitamins, fishmeal, and fish oil.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "Fishmeal is a key ingredient in salmon farming feed, while fish oil is essential in aquaculture feeds to provide necessary fatty acids.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "Vitamins are added nutrients in compound feed, which can help reduce the use of fishmeal and fish oil.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming can have health concerns associated with it, such as the accumulation of pollutants in fish with high fat content.", "citations": {"de9f2e6e-6769-4635-a399-58552e6eb27d_165935816": 1.0}}, {"text": "Farmed salmon can contain more Omega 3 than wild salmon due to the use of fish oil in their feed, but vegetable oils are also used as a cheaper and more sustainable alternative.", "citations": {"e9e0e25f-b317-4e99-8bf7-431ab1e290be_110862371": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming is governed by various standards and regulations, which can vary by country, but the goal is to ensure the health and safety of both the fish and the consumers.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0}}, {"text": "In Norway, the use of additives in salmon farming is regulated by the Aquaculture Act, which includes standards for additives used in feed.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Aquaculture Stewardship Council has a standard for salmon farming, which includes guidelines for additive use.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The RSPCA has welfare standards for farmed Atlantic salmon, which may include guidelines for additive use.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "In China, the use of additives in salmon farming is regulated by the Food Safety Law, which standardizes food additive use and storage.", "citations": {"9201cd2f-c818-467a-bd7a-c8e3f5315347_605116233": 1.0}}, {"text": "The General Administration of Market Supervision regulates food additive use, including in salmon farming, and ensures that food additives are stored separately from food products.", "citations": {"9201cd2f-c818-467a-bd7a-c8e3f5315347_605116233": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming can have environmental impacts, such as pollution and waste, and reducing their use can have economic benefits, such as reducing the cost of feed.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "Compound feed can cut down on fish use and is cheaper, making it a more economical option for salmon farmers.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "China reduced feed-grade fish use by 77 percent in some aquaculture trials, which can help reduce the environmental impact of salmon farming.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "Replacing feed-grade fish with compound feed can reduce pollution and protect vulnerable ocean ecosystems.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "The economic value of salmon aquaculture can be affected by the use of additives, and reducing their use can help maintain a healthy and sustainable industry.", "citations": {"7f15aa3b-2c6a-42d3-b23b-d01d8602d365_1058011567": 1.0}}, {"text": "Land-based salmon farming can reduce marine pollution and is a more sustainable option for the industry.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "Atlantic Sapphire built a large land salmon farm in Florida, which can help reduce the environmental impact of salmon farming.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "Microbubble oxygenation reduces marine pollution and increases growth rate, making it a viable option for salmon farmers.", "citations": {"df0754b4-3eed-49c2-a80a-ff78f49dcdc3_57274837": 1.0}}, {"text": "Microbubble technology reduces pollution and increases seafood production, which can help minimize the need for additives.", "citations": {"df0754b4-3eed-49c2-a80a-ff78f49dcdc3_57274837": 1.0}}, {"text": "Domestic feed production can help reduce the use of additives, and domestic feed contains 40% raw protein and essential amino acids.", "citations": {"23d7fe7e-4589-40b8-b911-e83020b3b80b_318736858": 1.0}}, {"text": "Domestic feed can be used in industrial and private water farms, making it a more sustainable option for the industry.", "citations": {"23d7fe7e-4589-40b8-b911-e83020b3b80b_318736858": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the use of additives in salmon farming is a complex issue that requires careful consideration of the potential risks and benefits, as well as the development of effective regulatory frameworks to ensure consumer safety and promote sustainable aquaculture practices.", "citations": {"194ab6fb-492b-4134-a822-790a0de32cff_117588944": 1.0}}, {"text": "The detection of additives in salmon feed and tissue is a crucial aspect of ensuring the safety and quality of farmed salmon, and modern methods such as DNA macrobarcode technology and real-time fluorescent PCR are being used for this purpose.", "citations": {"9f0b47e8-f7ed-47d4-8041-cd3e5f66b978_372353895": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of probiotics, such as Lactic Acid Bacillus B4, in salmon farming has been shown to improve fish growth and immunity.", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 1.0}}, {"text": "Probiotics like Lactic Acid Bacillus B4 also produce glucan, which increases probiotics and regulates immunity in fish when sucrose is added.", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 1.0}}, {"text": "The addition of yogurt feed containing Lactic Acid Bacillus B4 to the diet of fish for 2 months has been found to reduce disease and increase fish weight.", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 1.0}}, {"text": "Farmed salmon may contain polychlorinated biphenyls (PCBs) and artificial toxins, which are harmful to human health.", "citations": {"7d83d8ec-92b3-4bab-877a-977a3dc104c7_795166743": 1.0}}, {"text": "Farmed salmon has higher PCB levels than wild salmon, with PCB levels being 8 times higher in farmed salmon.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0}}, {"text": "Eating farmed salmon may increase cancer risk due to the high levels of PCBs present in the fish.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0}}, {"text": "High PCB concentrations in farmed salmon can double the risk of prostate cancer in men.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0}}, {"text": "The consumption of farmed salmon with high levels of additives can have negative health effects on the immune and nervous systems.", "citations": {"7d83d8ec-92b3-4bab-877a-977a3dc104c7_795166743": 1.0}}, {"text": "The excess fat in farmed salmon can accumulate pollutants, making it a less healthy option for human consumption.", "citations": {"de9f2e6e-6769-4635-a399-58552e6eb27d_165935816": 1.0}}, {"text": "Farmed salmon can contain more Omega 3 than wild salmon, but the use of vegetable oils in feed can reduce the Omega 3 content.", "citations": {"e9e0e25f-b317-4e99-8bf7-431ab1e290be_110862371": 1.0}}, {"text": "The variable feed used in salmon farming can affect the nutritional content of farmed salmon, making it essential to regulate and monitor feed quality.", "citations": {"e9e0e25f-b317-4e99-8bf7-431ab1e290be_110862371": 1.0}}, {"text": "Reducing additives in salmon farming can mitigate environmental degradation.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0}}, {"text": "IMTA systems reduce excess food and feces in water, which can help minimize the need for additives.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mussels remove up to 54% of salmon waste materials, and oarweed removes soluble nutrients from the water column, reducing the need for additives.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0}}, {"text": "Integrated multi-trophic aquaculture is a sustainable method that can reduce the need for antibiotics and additives.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming can harm the environment, and reducing their use can have economic benefits, such as reducing the cost of feed.", "citations": {"ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735": 1.0}}, {"text": "The economic value of salmon aquaculture can be affected by the use of additives, and reducing their use can help maintain a healthy and sustainable industry.", "citations": {"7f15aa3b-2c6a-42d3-b23b-d01d8602d365_1058011567": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tasmania's fisheries and aquaculture contributed $800 million to the economy in 2020-21, and reducing additive use can help maintain this economic value.", "citations": {"7f15aa3b-2c6a-42d3-b23b-d01d8602d365_1058011567": 1.0}}, {"text": "Strategies to minimize additive use include implementing IMTA systems, using microbubble oxygenation, and producing domestic feed.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0, "df0754b4-3eed-49c2-a80a-ff78f49dcdc3_57274837": 0.5, "23d7fe7e-4589-40b8-b911-e83020b3b80b_318736858": 0.25}}, {"text": "These strategies can help maintain fish health and growth rates while reducing the environmental impact of salmon farming.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0, "df0754b4-3eed-49c2-a80a-ff78f49dcdc3_57274837": 0.5, "23d7fe7e-4589-40b8-b911-e83020b3b80b_318736858": 0.25}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming is regulated by standards and regulations in countries such as Norway, Scotland, and China.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Fish Feed and Additives market has key players like Aller Aqua AS and Biomar AS, which can help drive the development of more sustainable feed options.", "citations": {"de2d157d-90d4-4aea-952a-02a3d9239115_107102801": 1.0}}, {"text": "The market size and growth rate of the Fish Feed and Additives market are analyzed over the forecast period, which can help identify trends and opportunities for reducing additive use.", "citations": {"de2d157d-90d4-4aea-952a-02a3d9239115_107102801": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the use of additives in salmon farming is a complex issue that requires careful consideration of the potential risks and benefits, as well as the development of effective regulatory frameworks to ensure consumer safety and promote sustainable aquaculture practices.", "citations": {"194ab6fb-492b-4134-a822-790a0de32cff_117588944": 1.0}}], "references": ["ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171", "23d7fe7e-4589-40b8-b911-e83020b3b80b_318736858", "7d83d8ec-92b3-4bab-877a-977a3dc104c7_795166743", "ced34f0a-144c-4eec-afab-98de204f3bfe_726039735", "8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648", "df0754b4-3eed-49c2-a80a-ff78f49dcdc3_57274837", "de9f2e6e-6769-4635-a399-58552e6eb27d_165935816", "e9e0e25f-b317-4e99-8bf7-431ab1e290be_110862371", "7b6d93af-b92a-4b45-887d-a325a2c58a8a_905125272", "de2d157d-90d4-4aea-952a-02a3d9239115_107102801", "206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288", "997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922", "39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469", "9201cd2f-c818-467a-bd7a-c8e3f5315347_605116233", "7f15aa3b-2c6a-42d3-b23b-d01d8602d365_1058011567", "194ab6fb-492b-4134-a822-790a0de32cff_117588944", "9f0b47e8-f7ed-47d4-8041-cd3e5f66b978_372353895"]}
