{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1077", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Javier Milei, Argentina's President, has introduced economic reforms including dollarization, privatization, and abolishing the Central Bank.", "citations": {"0c807e00-49d4-4d11-9f61-28bd7d910b30_66376477": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei's economic plan aims to liberalize the economy through privatization, deregulation, and export liberalization.", "citations": {"08d63595-1789-413d-9e6d-b22cf4bbc7ff_539685673": 1.0}}, {"text": "The reforms carry significant risks, including financial instability, social inequality, and national sovereignty concerns.", "citations": {"5468bde7-301d-4844-a2d0-6d03f040c12e_828775577": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei's government has introduced measures to support his reforms, including regulatory frameworks, reduced ministries, and austerity measures.", "citations": {"c1d0da66-16aa-4a2a-8f32-36dd0555f8c3_185829324": 1.0}}, {"text": "The IMF will disburse $4.7 billion to Argentina to support government reforms amid a severe economic crisis.", "citations": {"c1d0da66-16aa-4a2a-8f32-36dd0555f8c3_185829324": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei's policies have been opposed by labor unions and others, who argue they will harm workers' rights and national sovereignty.", "citations": {"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279": 1.0}}, {"text": "Argentina's economy faces significant challenges, making Milei's reforms crucial to address high inflation, a large fiscal deficit, and declining industrial production.", "citations": {"f1f16c1c-1e25-4224-8ccb-b455374573c5_362692412": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei's government lacks a majority in parliament and faces opposition that could block his policies and lead to hyperinflation.", "citations": {"5468bde7-301d-4844-a2d0-6d03f040c12e_828775577": 1.0}}, {"text": "The IMF has restarted its $4.7 billion program in Argentina, but default remains likely due to Milei's refusal to alter his economic prom