{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1078", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Javier Milei, the new president of Argentina, has introduced a series of economic reforms aimed at reducing the country's fiscal deficit and controlling inflation, including the privatization of state-owned entities and the weakening of labor protection.", "citations": {"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei's economic reforms have sparked opposition from trade unions, who argue that they will hurt the poor and vulnerable populations, such as low-income households and small businesses.", "citations": {"262765a4-72f4-4475-9a99-4e18d21d394f_13273279": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has introduced some measures to support low-income households, such as social subsidies and a credit fund of 3.5 billion pesos for small and medium-sized enterprises.", "citations": {"a69b6106-f7cd-4c8c-8c18-02bef9394e15_77398645": 1.0}}, {"text": "Argentina's inflation rate has soared to over 140%, and the poverty rate is over 40%, making economic reform a pressing issue.", "citations": {"58c21ede-b496-40c4-bd1d-1ce85e6a9b90_811607315": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei's reforms aim to achieve a zero budget deficit next year, and include measures such as increasing export duties, privatizing state-owned companies, and deregulating the economy.", "citations": {"9fb78d5e-18e3-488f-9d85-fa0cc4f7e79b_904219577": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has also announced plans to cut social spending and shut down the central bank, which may have significant consequences for the country's economy.", "citations": {"f1f16c1c-1e25-4224-8ccb-b455374573c5_362692412": 1.0}}, {"text": "Milei's economic reforms have been met with significant opposition, including nationwide protests and strikes, with many arguing that they will exacerbate poverty and inequality.", "citations": {"47d524e1-7d23-4076-a1f7-b3a8028577b2_347678882": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Inter