{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1081", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Quantum computing is a rapidly developing field with the potential to solve complex problems beyond classical computers' capabilities.", "citations": {"4ee4721f-48f4-4899-9582-498b25d7d691_301587801": 1.0}}, {"text": "China has developed a third-generation autonomous superconducting quantum computer with 198 qubits, including 72 working qubits.", "citations": {"4ee4721f-48f4-4899-9582-498b25d7d691_301587801": 1.0}}, {"text": "IBM, Google, and Taiwan are key players in quantum technology, with significant advancements in quantum computing.", "citations": {"c31154e1-a686-4216-adbd-6d0234ca034a_120455992": 1.0}}, {"text": "Countries like Taiwan and Russia are investing heavily in quantum computing, with Russia developing a four-qubit quantum ion computer prototype and qudits.", "citations": {"d68316b3-619f-4f48-a8cf-2e176581771c_469467575": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum error correction, crucial for practical quantum computers, has seen significant progress, including the development of codes like Shor and Bacon-Shor.", "citations": {"765f6998-50e6-42d0-b3c8-ed3d39896f44_511622726": 1.0}}, {"text": "Google and IBM have achieved quantum supremacy using their Sycamore and Eagle processors, respectively.", "citations": {"a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224": 1.0}}, {"text": "China achieved quantum supremacy with the Zuchongzhi processor, featuring superconducting qubits with 99% accuracy.", "citations": {"a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing, which could revolutionize fields like medicine and finance, is being heavily invested in by countries such as the US, China, and Germany.", "citations": {"5c91116a-b8e8-4dea-ac8c-79d1268af8e8_300084147": 1.0, "9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b_399146656": 0.5, "e6ada9b5-b0ba-4d18-a6ef-4f4330d20a5a_900469158": 0.25}}, {"text": "Quantum computing differs from traditional devices and requires optimal methods to aid AI algorithm development.", "citations": {"889275e3-4946-4d7c-beb9-15f82e75a042_491531089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The current quantum computing landscape is limited, requiring specialized skills and training.", "citations": {"a03708a7-1109-4597-9280-dcfd24e63e3b_731060815": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing integrates with AI and machine learning, and has applications in communication and coding systems.", "citations": {"a03708a7-1109-4597-9280-dcfd24e63e3b_731060815": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing may revolutionize industries like finance, pharmaceuticals, and automotive.", "citations": {"604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computers can solve problems faster and simulate complex reactions accurately, but require near absolute zero temperature.", "citations": {"604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593": 1.0}}, {"text": "Researchers and companies, including Keysight and Q-CTRL, are integrating quantum computing with AI, machine learning, and IoT to accelerate quantum processor development.", "citations": {"488c006a-23f8-40c5-81f0-bad8ef9f9164_827631176": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing is a rapidly evolving field expected to significantly impact various industries.", "citations": {"5c91116a-b8e8-4dea-ac8c-79d1268af8e8_300084147": 1.0, "9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b_399146656": 0.5, "e6ada9b5-b0ba-4d18-a6ef-4f4330d20a5a_900469158": 0.25}}], "references": ["889275e3-4946-4d7c-beb9-15f82e75a042_491531089", "5c91116a-b8e8-4dea-ac8c-79d1268af8e8_300084147", "a03708a7-1109-4597-9280-dcfd24e63e3b_731060815", "604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593", "4ee4721f-48f4-4899-9582-498b25d7d691_301587801", "9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b_399146656", "765f6998-50e6-42d0-b3c8-ed3d39896f44_511622726", "e6ada9b5-b0ba-4d18-a6ef-4f4330d20a5a_900469158", "d68316b3-619f-4f48-a8cf-2e176581771c_469467575", "488c006a-23f8-40c5-81f0-bad8ef9f9164_827631176"