{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1082", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Quantum computing is advancing rapidly, with significant successes in developing qubit technologies like superconducting qubits, ion traps, and silicon spin qubits.", "citations": {"a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224": 1.0}}, {"text": "China leads in quantum technology, with Zuchongzhi No. 2 computing 10 million times faster than traditional computers.", "citations": {"75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US, China, and Japan are investing heavily in quantum computing, led by companies like IBM, Google, and Fujitsu.", "citations": {"75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028": 1.0, "a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224": 0.5, "ae28acd5-2f02-413e-8c60-40842946fe97_510976926": 0.25}}, {"text": "IBM has reduced the qubits required for error correction by a factor of 10 using a new approach.", "citations": {"4d5e6fac-834b-4526-a7c1-a5be27446277_703470420": 1.0}}, {"text": "Google has developed new quantum error correction algorithms using a 49-qubit design with increasing array size and reduced error rate.", "citations": {"e46ecccd-fed2-4d87-b426-e8abb60748cc_682028010": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum error correction is crucial for quantum computing as it extends the lifetime of quantum information past the breakeven point.", "citations": {"a50e520c-6ba4-445c-ba2a-565b4a0794e4_368273242": 1.0}}, {"text": "Current quantum computers have high error rates and qubits last only 30 to 95 milliseconds, limiting practical applications.", "citations": {"75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing can bring breakthroughs in fields like drug discovery, financial modeling, and optimization.", "citations": {"adb6cf9f-7fe4-4023-9f10-658f680033f7_120209203": 1.0}}, {"text": "Qubit Pharmaceuticals uses quantum computing for drug discovery through simulation and molecular modeling to co-develop new drugs.", "citations": {"a924c5d7-8148-4739-91e4-ee2d681ce88c_136715806": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mercedes-Benz and ExxonMobil are using quantum computing for battery development and fuel routing, respectively.", "citations": {"604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing is being used in financial modeling to optimize risk assessment and portfolio optimization.", "citations": {"24c3878d-8256-4d04-bf56-225b8ffa82c6_711020926": 1.0}}, {"text": "Fujitsu has developed a 64-qubit quantum computer for drug discovery and finance using superconductivity.", "citations": {"ae28acd5-2f02-413e-8c60-40842946fe97_510976926": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing can accelerate machine learning, improve training efficiency and accuracy, and solve currently unsolvable complex problems.", "citations": {"24c3878d-8256-4d04-bf56-225b8ffa82c6_711020926": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing has limitations, including the need for robust error correction and sensitivity to extreme temperatures.", "citations": {"604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593": 1.0}}, {"text": "Finland is investing heavily in quantum computing for industry use.", "citations": {"b66d0211-a8df-41ef-ad2f-fe0bea54c328_288204630": 1.0}}, {"text": "Germany has launched Europe's first 5,000 qubits quantum computer.", "citations": {"3730cc8b-2e9b-47d2-a1fe-d64c9c17aee3_1066113091": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing has the potential to revolutionize industries like finance, pharmaceuticals, and logistics, prompting heavy investment from countries and companies.", "citations": {"0d2cd431-b3cb-42ca-865a-92042fe808ad_738541105": 1.0, "3730cc8b-2e9b-47d2-a1fe-d64c9c17aee3_1066113091": 0.5, "e002e960-91b9-4fa1-9e1e-031d1a1aea64_946882655": 0.25}}, {"text": "Quantum computing is expected to bring $850 billion in benefits by 2035, but also poses significant risks.", "citations": {"dfd8d281-9f71-4a30-ae82-db3aa48c12d9_762628746": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computers can break certain classical and public-key encryption algorithms by 2030, posing a threat to data security.", "citations": {"62d2e66f-0a27-4f2d-b5aa-134e0cdd4870_85611703": 1.0}}, {"text": "The transition to a quantum-resistant world will require years, significant investment, and upgrading or replacing over 20 billion devices.", "citations": {"80d92c30-b1d7-4be0-b9e0-60cd537af959_122870528": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computers can decrypt data at a later time, posing a significant concern for companies and governments.", "citations": {"9084e22e-ce0b-4dd3-a56c-6f237bbaca81_176734587": 1.0}}, {"text": "Many countries and companies are investing heavily in quantum-resistant cryptography and key distribution research.", "citations": {"eb506222-d25f-4139-92ca-4cbfe3e0209b_944083026": 1.0}}, {"text": "NIST has introduced new post-quantum cryptography algorithms and quantum key distribution can utilize existing fiber-optic cables.", "citations": {"eb506222-d25f-4139-92ca-4cbfe3e0209b_944083026": 1.0}}, {"text": "A hybrid approach combining post-quantum cryptography, quantum key distribution, and photon entanglement may provide a more comprehensive secure communication solution.", "citations": {"eb506222-d25f-4139-92ca-4cbfe3e0209b_944083026": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum-safe infrastructure, including post-quantum cryptography and related technologies, may not be achieved until the 2030s-2040s.", "citations": {"eb506222-d25f-4139-92ca-4cbfe3e0209b_944083026": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing is being used to solve optimization problems, including with the MaxCut algorithm.", "citations": {"1af86f52-5ab8-4239-8202-f264c8702abf_230442744": 1.0}}, {"text": "Nvidia's cuQuantum simulated 1688 qubits on 896 GPUs, achieving 96% of the best-known answers.", "citations": {"1af86f52-5ab8-4239-8202-f264c8702abf_230442744": 1.0}}, {"text": "The cuQuantum platform uses cuTensorNet, a library that has set a world record in quantum simulation.", "citations": {"1af86f52-5ab8-4239-8202-f264c8702abf_230442744": 1.0}}, {"text": "D-Wave has built Europe's first 5,000 qubit quantum computer to solve optimization problems.", "citations": {"3730cc8b-2e9b-47d2-a1fe-d64c9c17aee3_1066113091": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum annealing offers higher system stability and is used in applications like drug development and cybersecurity.", "citations": {"3730cc8b-2e9b-47d2-a1fe-d64c9c17aee3_1066113091": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Digital Annealing Algorithm accelerates material screening by 10x and solves combination optimization problems.", "citations": {"aaa78c5d-9c60-456c-8b42-b8c0f7a65700_689952675": 1.0}}, {"text": "QUBO is a commonly used algorithm for optimization problems, including cyclic compound screening.", "citations": {"aaa78c5d-9c60-456c-8b42-b8c0f7a65700_689952675": 1.0}}, {"text": "Google scientists devised an algorithm to translate physical problems into quantum language for quantum computers.", "citations": {"b98a30f4-57d3-4c74-a49f-c0e3262cfad4_87578461": 1.0}}, {"text": "The algorithm exponentially increases operation speed on quantum computers and describes wave-like systems, including neuronal activity maps.", "citations": {"b98a30f4-57d3-4c74-a49f-c0e3262cfad4_87578461": 1.0}}, {"text": "China Mobile is using quantum computing for antenna optimization and 6G research.", "citations": {"ccafa886-e3dd-4385-a77b-18ff9f796afa_726203446": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Quantum algorithm is used for 5G and large-scale network optimization.", "citations": {"ccafa886-e3dd-4385-a77b-18ff9f796afa_726203446": 1.0}}, {"text": "Russia is improving quantum algorithms and plans to build a universal quantum computer by 2024.", "citations": {"d68316b3-619f-4f48-a8cf-2e176581771c_469467575": 1.0}}, {"text": "Qudits increase quantum computer performance and allow for denser data encoding.", "citations": {"d68316b3-619f-4f48-a8cf-2e176581771c_469467575": 1.0}}, {"text": "Grover's algorithm is a quantum algorithm used for searching databases and other applications.", "citations": {"d68316b3-619f-4f48-a8cf-2e176581771c_469467575": 1.0}}, {"text": "QPSO is being combined with LSTM for optimized prediction.", "citations": {"ee2934df-bbbd-43ce-855c-9806b55a1431_438650748": 1.0}}, {"text": "The QPSO-LSTM algorithm outperforms ARIMA, BP, and RNNs in time series prediction.", "citations": {"ee2934df-bbbd-43ce-855c-9806b55a1431_438650748": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing is being applied to fields like physics, chemistry, and materials science to solve complex problems.", "citations": {"e7c1fd1f-daf1-45e2-a485-62cd20dd50d8_642767079": 1.0}}, {"text": "The time evolution operator is key to quantum algorithms and has applications in condensed matter physics and quantum chemistry.", "citations": {"e7c1fd1f-daf1-45e2-a485-62cd20dd50d8_642767079": 1.0}}, {"text": "New algorithms accelerate the time evolution operator workload, enabling simpler quantum computers.", "citations": {"e7c1fd1f-daf1-45e2-a485-62cd20dd50d8_642767079": 1.0}}, {"text": "Hybrid quantum and classical methods improve performance and reduce costs for complex problems.", "citations": {"e7c1fd1f-daf1-45e2-a485-62cd20dd50d8_642767079": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing faces enormous challenges in scalability, reliability, and error correction.", "citations": {"75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028": 1.0}}, {"text": "Researchers found a way to control qubits using microwaves and light, meeting DiVincenzo standards for scalable quantum computers.", "citations": {"3edb8337-01a0-4624-8117-375dd646d7b3_976418897": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computers require large-scale processors and precise qubit control for optimal performance.", "citations": {"3edb8337-01a0-4624-8117-375dd646d7b3_976418897": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing is expensive, with a single qubit costing up to $10,000, but companies like IBM and others are already using it.", "citations": {"604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computers can solve problems faster than classical computers, but their reliability is compromised by inaccurate results.", "citations": {"604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computers lack error correction and can decrypt secure data with their processing power.", "citations": {"604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593": 1.0}}, {"text": "Global investment in quantum computing has topped $35.5 billion.", "citations": {"0d2cd431-b3cb-42ca-865a-92042fe808ad_738541105": 1.0}}, {"text": "The UK has allocated \u00a32.5 billion for quantum research.", "citations": {"0d2cd431-b3cb-42ca-865a-92042fe808ad_738541105": 1.0}}, {"text": "Europe's first quantum computer with over 5,000 qubits was launched in Germany.", "citations": {"3730cc8b-2e9b-47d2-a1fe-d64c9c17aee3_1066113091": 1.0}}, {"text": "Fujitsu has developed Japan's No. 2 quantum computer for drug and finance applications.", "citations": {"ae28acd5-2f02-413e-8c60-40842946fe97_510976926": 1.0}}, {"text": "Huayi Quantum is developing a 100-200 qubit ion-trap quantum computer and a quantum computing cloud platform.", "citations": {"d574607d-738d-4b79-a7fe-65e052c89058_117378038": 1.0}}, {"text": "Fujitsu will offer quantum computers to enterprises in 2023 for financial forecasting and drug development.", "citations": {"e002e960-91b9-4fa1-9e1e-031d1a1aea64_946882655": 1.0}}, {"text": "Pfizer and Japan's AIST are building a quantum supercomputer for drug research and logistics.", "citations": {"e55577c7-6929-4914-8bd3-894444393660_683111040": 1.0}}, {"text": "Fujitsu and RIKEN have developed a 64-qubit quantum computer for applications in medicine and finance.", "citations": {"e7fec63e-2ee1-4eb1-8d3e-4b228c85ce1a_1041098481": 1.0}}, {"text": "The UK, Germany, and Japan are investing heavily in quantum computing research and development.", "citations": {"0d2cd431-b3cb-42ca-865a-92042fe808ad_738541105": 1.0, "3730cc8b-2e9b-47d2-a1fe-d64c9c17aee3_1066113091": 0.5, "e002e960-91b9-4fa1-9e1e-031d1a1aea64_946882655": 0.25}}, {"text": "China has created a quantum computer prototype.", "citations": {"adb6cf9f-7fe4-4023-9f10-658f680033f7_120209203": 1.0}}, {"text": "Finland's QuTI project, with a EUR 10 million budget and 12 partners, showcases the country's commitment to quantum computing.", "citations": {"b66d0211-a8df-41ef-ad2f-fe0bea54c328_288204630": 1.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing has potential applications in drug discovery, financial modeling, and optimization problems.", "citations": {}}], "references": ["75da5acf-bc82-4304-8c5a-160725cfaa1d_729488028", "3edb8337-01a0-4624-8117-375dd646d7b3_976418897", "d68316b3-619f-4f48-a8cf-2e176581771c_469467575", "a924c5d7-8148-4739-91e4-ee2d681ce88c_136715806", "80d92c30-b1d7-4be0-b9e0-60cd537af959_122870528", "eb506222-d25f-4139-92ca-4cbfe3e0209b_944083026", "1af86f52-5ab8-4239-8202-f264c8702abf_230442744", "62d2e66f-0a27-4f2d-b5aa-134e0cdd4870_85611703", "604d8af2-a31d-40bc-b006-3d493d0ec076_131533593", "b98a30f4-57d3-4c74-a49f-c0e3262cfad4_87578461", "b66d0211-a8df-41ef-ad2f-fe0bea54c328_288204630", "ee2934df-bbbd-43ce-855c-9806b55a1431_438650748", "dfd8d281-9f71-4a30-ae82-db3aa48c12d9_762628746", "ccafa886-e3dd-4385-a77b-18ff9f796afa_726203446", "3730cc8b-2e9b-47d2-a1fe-d64c9c17aee3_1066113091", "adb6cf9f-7fe4-4023-9f10-658f680033f7_120209203", "a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224", "d574607d-738d-4b79-a7fe-65e052c89058_117378038", "ae28acd5-2f02-413e-8c60-40842946fe97_510976926", "24c3878d-8256-4d04-bf56-225b8ffa82c6_711020926", "4d5e6fac-834b-4526-a7c1-a5be27446277_703470420", "e46ecccd-fed2-4d87-b426-e8abb60748cc_682028010", "e7c1fd1f-daf1-45e2-a485-62cd20dd50d8_642767079", "e7fec63e-2ee1-4eb1-8d3e-4b228c85ce1a_1041098481", "aaa78c5d-9c60-456c-8b42-b8c0f7a65700_689952675", "e55577c7-6929-4914-8bd3-894444393660_683111040", "0d2cd431-b3cb-42ca-865a-92042fe808ad_738541105", "e002e960-91b9-4fa1-9e1e-031d1a1aea64_946882655", "a50e520c-6ba4-445c-ba2a-565b4a0794e4_368273242", "9084e22e-ce0b-4dd3-a56c-6f237bbaca81_176734587"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1083", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Woolly mammoths went extinct around 10,000 years ago due to climate change and human hunting.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change contributed to the extinction of woolly mammoths by altering their habitat.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0, "254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187": 0.5, "be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 0.25}}, {"text": "Human hunting contributed to the decline of woolly mammoths for their meat, ivory, and fur.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0, "44424d28-dcbb-4e8d-b7d3-46eee5796966_522924419": 0.5, "d0fdd296-9dbe-4774-a00b-b9fe01772cb1_668789018": 0.25}}, {"text": "Climate change and human hunting likely pushed the woolly mammoth population to the brink of extinction.", "citations": {"13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130": 1.0, "b6264f9c-84ed-41cc-ab9d-9467a86380dc_963536056": 0.5}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths significantly impacted the environment, reducing nutrient transport by over 90%.", "citations": {"775c0547-e910-4ef0-a7c5-6250da1ae3e7_245632462": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change led to the extinction of woolly mammoths, giant bears, dire wolves, and other megafauna around the same time.", "citations": {"254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187": 1.0, "be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 0.5}}, {"text": "Studying woolly mammoth extinction highlights the impact of human activity on the environment and biodiversity.", "citations": {"b5a29cf6-9bdc-45fc-89be-d5eff38511cd_445183438": 1.0, "e1ba78b5-5b7b-4b11-8309-852953855d8b_51752637": 0.5}}, {"text": "Human activity has driven the extinction of many species, including the woolly mammoth, at a rate 100 times higher than without humans.", "citations": {"775c0547-e910-4ef0-a7c5-6250da1ae3e7_245632462": 1.0}}, {"text": "Human activities, like hunting and habitat destruction, significantly contributed to the decline and extinction of woolly mammoths.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0}}, {"text": "The exact cause of woolly mammoth extinction is debated among scientists, with theories including climate change, human activity, and random events like disease outbreaks.", "citations": {"1998c5c4-f34b-4d7b-bfb3-a21ba3959a09_1013235632": 1.0, "c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691": 0.5}}, {"text": "Mammoth populations dwindled due to climate change after interacting with humans in Siberia for around 800 years.", "citations": {"d0fdd296-9dbe-4774-a00b-b9fe01772cb1_668789018": 1.0}}, {"text": "A 'mammoth graveyard' with 156 mammoths was found in East Siberian Arctic, dating human settlement to 11.2-12.4 kyr ago.", "citations": {"d0fdd296-9dbe-4774-a00b-b9fe01772cb1_668789018": 1.0}}, {"text": "Woolly mammoths became extinct due to insufficient food caused by climate warming and reduced vegetation.", "citations": {"f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426": 1.0}}, {"text": "A warming climate changed vegetation, replacing mammoth habitats, and humans used their bones and tusks to make tools and instruments.", "citations": {"f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426": 1.0}}, {"text": "Studying woolly mammoth extinction informs us about climate change's impact on modern ecosystems and biodiversity conservation.", "citations": {"b5a29cf6-9bdc-45fc-89be-d5eff38511cd_445183438": 1.0}}, {"text": "Analyzing human migration patterns and their correlation with climate change and woolly mammoth extinction can provide valuable insights into human activity, environmental change, and species extinction.", "citations": {"41a8ca99-dd05-451b-b7c8-3d29e51a1e70_183334978": 1.0}}], "references": ["074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440", "254efa47-8edb-4f23-8178-8fc850a8ea29_987207187", "d0fdd296-9dbe-4774-a00b-b9fe01772cb1_668789018", "b6264f9c-84ed-41cc-ab9d-9467a86380dc_963536056", "f59dc840-8a51-49ca-a687-2f0a97d918ca_227922426", "775c0547-e910-4ef0-a7c5-6250da1ae3e7_245632462", "41a8ca99-dd05-451b-b7c8-3d29e51a1e70_183334978", "be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929", "b5a29cf6-9bdc-45fc-89be-d5eff38511cd_445183438", "44424d28-dcbb-4e8d-b7d3-46eee5796966_522924419", "1998c5c4-f34b-4d7b-bfb3-a21ba3959a09_1013235632", "13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130", "c1e6db3c-0326-4e04-a106-0a4c7aad96bb_386798691", "e1ba78b5-5b7b-4b11-8309-852953855d8b_51752637"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1084", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "The woolly mammoths went extinct around 10,000 years ago due to a combination of climate change and human hunting, with both factors contributing to the decline of the species.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change played a significant role in the extinction of woolly mammoths, as it reduced the availability of food resources for the mammoths, making them more vulnerable to human hunting.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}, {"text": "Human hunting is believed to have put additional pressure on the already vulnerable mammoth populations, with hunters targeting the animals at predictable locations.", "citations": {"13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130": 1.0}}, {"text": "The high mobility of the woolly mammoths may have actually hastened their extinction, as they were forced to travel longer distances in search of food and shelter, making them more vulnerable to human hunting.", "citations": {"13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130": 1.0}}, {"text": "The closest relative of the woolly mammoth, the African elephant, is still found in Africa today, but the woolly mammoth itself has been extinct for around 10,000 years.", "citations": {"b5a29cf6-9bdc-45fc-89be-d5eff38511cd_445183438": 1.0}}, {"text": "The loss of woolly mammoths had significant effects on ecosystem processes and biodiversity, including a decrease in seed distribution and nutrient cycling, leading to a decrease in ecosystem productivity.", "citations": {"1998c5c4-f34b-4d7b-bfb3-a21ba3959a09_1013235632": 1.0}}, {"text": "The extinction of woolly mammoths decreased phosphorus redistribution by 90%, highlighting the significant impact of their loss on ecosystem processes.", "citations": {"1998c5c4-f34b-4d7b-bfb3-a21ba3959a09_1013235632": 1.0}}, {"text": "The disappearance of megafauna, including woolly mammoths, led to a decrease in nutrient distribution, which had cascading effects on ecosystem biodiversity.", "citations": {"6e875fd5-8b9f-4a3c-89e3-c522ed5d041d_983323011": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change played a crucial role in the extinction of woolly mammoths, with rapid climate change leading to scarcity of food and failure to adapt to changing landscape and flora.", "citations": {"be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929": 1.0}}, {"text": "The study of the woolly mammoths' extinction highlights the need to consider wildlife and livestock in mitigating wildfires and maintaining ecosystem biodiversity.", "citations": {"d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613": 1.0}}, {"text": "The loss of woolly mammoths had significant effects on the population dynamics and extinction risk of other species within their ecosystems, including the collapse of predators and the loss of fruit trees.", "citations": {"d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the extinction of woolly mammoths was a complex event that was driven by a combination of factors, including climate change and human hunting, and had significant and far-reaching consequences for ecosystem processes and biodiversity.", "citations": {"074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440": 1.0}}], "references": ["13ea93b3-b90a-433c-83f5-d01dbdf2cf08_453229130", "1998c5c4-f34b-4d7b-bfb3-a21ba3959a09_1013235632", "b5a29cf6-9bdc-45fc-89be-d5eff38511cd_445183438", "6e875fd5-8b9f-4a3c-89e3-c522ed5d041d_983323011", "d76d6355-7ef9-4943-8e78-7de26d4c07c7_668357613", "074b2976-a44d-4f0e-a2e7-dbdf8e0f8b07_764530440", "be519fc5-23ef-46e4-83ae-d3f777ba3cfc_4783929"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1085", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Greenland holds around 10% of the world's rare earth mineral reserves.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Guanast deposit in southern Greenland has the world's second-largest rare earth reserves.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Tanbreez mine in Greenland contains an estimated 19 million tons of rare earth oxides, including heavy rare earth elements used in electric vehicles and wind turbines.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland's possible deposits are found in the Kuannersuit region and the Surftog Carbonatite complex, which contain rare earth minerals including neodymium and praseodymium.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0, "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 0.5}}, {"text": "Extracting these minerals can be difficult and often harmful, posing environmental concerns and health risks.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0, "be0e1159-bd31-403e-acf1-b495b0455519_773343369": 0.5}}, {"text": "China and companies like AEX Gold, NEO, and KoBold Metals are developing means to extract and exploit these minerals.", "citations": {"3eccce76-e73e-4d99-8cbc-2a07d9b3e61e_540589932": 1.0, "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 0.5, "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 0.25}}, {"text": "Greenland's rare earth reserves are estimated to be worth billions of dollars.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Extraction in Greenland is challenging due to the harsh Arctic climate, which requires special equipment.", "citations": {"3b7c1d89-eff0-4f23-897a-d21aaedc4a5d_356974021": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Greenlandic government has prioritized environmental concerns, banning uranium mining and revoking inactive or unpaid licenses.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0, "cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 0.5}}, {"text": "Investing in Greenland's rare earth minerals requires careful consideration and a commitment to responsible practices.", "citations": {"3eccce76-e73e-4d99-8cbc-2a07d9b3e61e_540589932": 1.0, "cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 0.5, "e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 0.25}}, {"text": "The country's rare earth minerals could play a key role in the global industry as the EU seeks to reduce its reliance on China.", "citations": {"6afe4f2a-2615-4a87-aa84-962843e7e858_940628298": 1.0}}, {"text": "The development of Arctic rare earth projects, including in Greenland, is hindered by environmental concerns, but rapid ice melt due to the climate crisis is increasing access to potential mineral deposits.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "The investment in KoBold Metals is backed by billionaires Gates, Bezos, and Bloomberg, due to growing interest in Greenland's mineral resources.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0, "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436": 0.5}}, {"text": "Mining in Greenland could diversify the economy and create jobs, but requires sustainable methods to mitigate environmental concerns.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0, "3eccce76-e73e-4d99-8cbc-2a07d9b3e61e_540589932": 0.5}}], "references": ["4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299", "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907", "3b7c1d89-eff0-4f23-897a-d21aaedc4a5d_356974021", "95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580", "fab5960e-59f4-40c6-be6e-a0afdb90a201_1010336436", "cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089", "841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424", "3eccce76-e73e-4d99-8cbc-2a07d9b3e61e_540589932", "6afe4f2a-2615-4a87-aa84-962843e7e858_940628298", "be0e1159-bd31-403e-acf1-b495b0455519_773343369", "e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "attract", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1086", "run_id": "attract-biological"}, "responses": [{"text": "Greenland has significant rare earth mineral reserves, potentially accounting for 10% of global production.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland's rare earth minerals include neodymium and praseodymium, used in electric vehicles and wind turbines.", "citations": {"583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Kuannersuit region in Greenland is home to one of the world's largest rare earth mines.", "citations": {"841bf963-f828-4462-a15e-2a86a5f30e39_815508424": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Surfertog project in Greenland contains significant neodymium and praseodymium deposits.", "citations": {"583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 1.0}}, {"text": "The ease of extracting rare earth minerals in Greenland varies by location and deposit type.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Extraction of rare earth minerals in Greenland is challenging due to environmental concerns.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Several countries and corporations, including AEX Gold, NEO, and Tanbreez Mining, are interested in extracting rare earth minerals in Greenland.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0, "583b2ca7-e877-4559-a77f-b879fa18b09d_623010907": 0.5, "95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 0.25}}, {"text": "China is interested in developing Greenland's rare earth deposits, with companies like Shenghe Resources investing in the mineral sector.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU has signed a strategic partnership with Greenland to develop sustainable rare earth mineral extraction projects.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "The partnership promotes high environmental and social standards in Greenland's mineral sector.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland's rare earth minerals can significantly support the global transition to renewable energy.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 1.0}}, {"text": "Rare earth mineral extraction in Greenland must be done sustainably to minimize environmental impacts and benefit local communities.", "citations": {"791b0315-efeb-409c-87df-83f353136384_778891498": 1.0}}, {"text": "Greenland's rare earth minerals, including the Guanast deposit, are valued at millions of dollars.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 1.0}}, {"text": "Rare earth mineral extraction in Greenland is expected to create jobs and stimulate economic growth.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "Rare earth mineral extraction in Greenland poses significant environmental costs, including radioactive waste and acid-containing sewage water.", "citations": {"696c9a8e-abc4-4b29-b004-c9684ba93c6d_966756918": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Greenlandic government has implemented regulations for responsible and sustainable mining with a focus on environmental protection and social responsibility.", "citations": {"2ab77c9a-c7c0-41df-b3b1-29e18129d1ca_249196879": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government has established a mining school to train local workers and create a skilled mineral sector workforce.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0}}, {"text": "Extracting rare earth minerals in Greenland could bring economic benefits, but also poses environmental and social challenges.", "citations": {"e251bb23-d330-4c8b-af1a-8f6c86ff3fcf_107535406": 1.0}}, {"text": "The country's geology and geography make it attractive for mining investments.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 1.0}}, {"text": "The government's poli